snippet.textDisplay: Hey DissociaDID - I've been watching your videos for a while now, and I'm so glad I found this channel. I've struggled with depression and suicidal thoughts a lot, and for a while I'd just felt like I was spiraling out of control. I'd spent a lot of the days I couldn't get out of bed watching people on YouTube talking about how they 'got through it' in the end, trying to find MY will to get through, you know? Well, YouTube recommended me a bunch of videos, and your Meet the Alters videos were in the mix. I've never really known anything about DID beyond the media sensationalism and so I started watching. I'm so thankful I did. I've learned so much from you guys, not just about DID but about being who you are and accepting the difficulties and learning to bounce back from hardships. Kyle makes me laugh so much! Nin is so sweet, and I'm absolutely fascinated watching Jade speak - she has such soothing mannerisms, and she's so articulate and level-headed. I'm super fond of Ruby and Sally too - they're completely different  alters but at the same time whenever I see them I'm instantly just 'UwU' (is that even a thing anymore? LOL). I'm doing a lot better now, and I just wanted to take the time to say thank you. It must be so hard to put yourselves out there and risk the vulnerability that comes with it, especially given recent events. You're all so inspiring, and I know not just to me personally. I don't know if any of you will read this, but I just wanted to put this out there. I'm sorry that there are people in this world that hurt children like the child you were - I'm sorry that you're still dealing with the fallout from such horror. I'm so sad and so desperately angry for you. But I'm also so awed by how you've been able to teach so many people about your lives and what it is like living with such a widely stigmatised disorder. Thank you for all that you've done, and hopefully continue to do. So many of us love you guys. I hope you're all doing okay! 💙💙💙
